    "narrative": "The core of today\u2019s offensive attack centers on **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts our highest individual efficiency score at 77.45. Despite a slight park penalty, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** draws a favorable matchup against a sub-optimal southpaw, and his spot in the three-hole provides the optimal environment for run production. Similarly, **Bryson Stott** (72.46) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (71.36) are prioritized as elite starts. **Bryson Stott** benefits immensely from a soft matchup against Assad, carrying a +19% boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill projection, while **Geraldo Perdomo**\u2019s outlook is bolstered by a +16% park factor and a premium batting order position. These three represent our most reliable avenues for daily production, as they effectively navigate their respective matchups to clear the 70-point threshold.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Yainer Diaz**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 38.75. While **Yainer Diaz** offers upside, the combination of a tough matchup against Kirby and a low spot in the batting order dropped him below our 40-point efficiency floor, signaling a day to prioritize roster preservation. Elsewhere, we are closely monitoring the weather, as the wind blowing out in several venues has provided a consistent +5% boost across much of the lineup, notably assisting **Taylor Ward** and **Jeremiah Jackson** in their outings against Nelson, R. We remain wary of **Lawrence Butler**, whose score of 59.69 is impressive but carries heightened risk due to an intimidating matchup against Eovaldi. With **Daulton Varsho**, **Tyler Freeman**, and **Jonathan Aranda** unavailable due to team off-days, our bench depth is currently limited, making the performance of starters like **Cal Raleigh**\u2014who carries a 54.61 despite a difficult park environment\u2014vital to maintaining our 5x5 Roto standing. We continue to monitor the status of **Matt Chapman**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** as potential future rotations should the current lineup stagnate.",
